recutils: recutils (utilities for text-based databases)
recutils:
recutils: GNU recutils is a set of tools and libraries to access human-editable,
recutils: text-based databases called recfiles.  The data is stored as a
recutils: sequence of records, each record containing an arbitrary number of
recutils: named fields.  Advanced capabilities usually found in other data
recutils: storage systems are supported by GNU recutils: data types, data
recutils: integrity (keys, mandatory fields, etc) as well as the ability of
recutils: records to refer to other records (sort of foreign keys).  Despite
recutils: its simplicity, recfiles can be used to store medium-sized databases.
recutils:
recutils: Packaged by Georgi D. Sotirov <gdsotirov@dir.bg>
